==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sacrarium
<hw>Sa*cra"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>-ria</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., fr. <ets>sacer</ets>
sacred.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sort of family chapel in the houses of
the Romans, devoted to a special divinity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The adytum of a temple.</def>
<rj><au>Gwilt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In a Christian church, the sanctuary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sacrate</ent>⟦br⟧
